    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document updates RFC 3161.  It allows the use of ESSCertIDv2, as defined in RFC 5035, to specify the hash of a signer certificate when the hash is calculated with a function other than the Secure Hash Algorithm (SHA-1). [STANDARDS-TRACK]&lt;/p&gt;</t>
